    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-05-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-05-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="500" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d500">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Peraza</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1890-05-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 19,
                                1890</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that I have
                            received a dispatch from our minister at London, reporting that, in
                            compliance with my instructions, of the transmission of which I advised
                            you on the 2d instant, he had an interview with Lord Salisbury in regard
                            to the renewal of diplomatic relations between Venezuela and Great
                            Britain and the settlement of the boundary dispute by arbitration.</p>
                <p>After listening to the views of this Government, His Lordship informed
                            Mr. Lincoln that he desired to consult with the colonial office before
                            replying to his suggestions.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James G. Blaine.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
